      "logo": { "@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://tallchairadvisor.com/images/og-default.jpg" }
    }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is the Herman Miller Aeron Size C good for tall people?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "The Aeron Size C fits tall users between roughly 6'0\" and 6'6\" with lean to average builds. Its fixed seat depth of 18.5\" and 20.5\" seat height ceiling can be limiting for users 6'4\"+ who need maximum seat depth adjustment. The Leap Plus accommodates taller users with more adjustability."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the main difference between the Aeron Size C and the Leap Plus?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "The biggest difference is seat depth: the Aeron Size C has a fixed seat depth of approximately 18.5\", while the Leap Plus adjusts from 15.75\" to 19.75\". The Aeron uses mesh for breathability; the Leap Plus uses upholstered foam. The Leap Plus also has a higher weight capacity (500 lbs vs 350 lbs) and wider seat."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which is better for hot climates or users who run warm — Aeron or Leap Plus?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "The Herman Miller Aeron is significantly better for users who run warm. Its 8Z Pellicle mesh allows airflow through the seat and back, preventing the heat buildup that occurs with foam-upholstered chairs like the Leap Plus. For warm climates or users who work in non-air-conditioned spaces, this difference is substantial."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can the Aeron Size C support a 250 lb tall person?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes. The Aeron Size C is rated to 350 lbs. A 250 lb user is well within the weight limit. The more relevant question is height and build proportions — the Aeron Size C has a narrower seat (20.75\") than the Leap Plus (22\"), which can feel snug for taller users with wider hip measurements."
        }
